---
import { Button, TextSection } from '@components/odyssey-theme';
import Layout from '../../layouts/Page.astro';
import HeroSection from '../../components/sections/heros/HeroSection.astro';
import CtaCardSection from '../../components/sections/CtaCardSection.astro';
import CompareWiseNav from '../../components/compare-wise/CompareWiseNav.astro';

const seo = {
	title: 'Q&A | Compare Wise',
	description:
		'Frequently asked questions about Compare Wise — the Shopify app for creating and managing product comparison tables.',
};
---

<Layout {seo}>
	<CompareWiseNav current="/compare-wise/qa" />
	<HeroSection>
		<div slot="text-container">
			<h1>Questions & Answers</h1>
			<p>
				Everything you need to know about Compare Wise. Can't find an
				answer? Reach out to our support team.
			</p>
		</div>
		<picture slot="image-container">
			<img
				src="/assets/images/compare-wise/hero.png"
				alt="Compare Wise Q&A"
				id="home-hero-image"
			/>
		</picture>
	</HeroSection>

	<TextSection narrow>
		<h2>Getting Started</h2>

		<h3>What is Compare Wise?</h3>
		<p>
			Compare Wise is a Shopify app that lets you create and manage
			product comparison tables directly from your Shopify admin panel. You
			can build feature-rich comparison tables — all without writing any code.
		</p>

		<h3>How do I install Compare Wise?</h3>
		<p>
			Visit the
			<a href="https://apps.shopify.com/compare-wise">Compare Wise page</a> on
			the Shopify App Store and click "Add app." The installation takes just a
			few clicks. Compare Wise installs as a theme extension, so your theme
			files are never modified.
		</p>

		<h3>Do I need coding knowledge to use Compare Wise?</h3>
		<p>
			No. Compare Wise is designed for merchants of all technical levels. The
			entire app runs through a visual dashboard — create tables, customize
		 designs, and publish with point-and-click controls.
		</p>

		<h3>Will Compare Wise work with my current Shopify theme?</h3>
		<p>
			Yes. Compare Wise uses Shopify's theme extension system, which is
			compatible with all Shopify Online Store 2.0 themes. It also works
			with many older themes. If you encounter compatibility issues, our
			support team can help.
		</p>

		<h2>Comparison Tables</h2>

		<h3>What types of comparison tables can I create?</h3>
		<p>
			Compare Wise supports flexible comparison table configurations:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Feature comparison tables</strong> — Compare products side by side with custom feature rows</li>
			<li><strong>Pricing tables</strong> — Display pricing tiers with highlighted recommended plans</li>
			<li><strong>Spec tables</strong> — Technical specifications comparison for detailed product data</li>
			<li><strong>Plan comparison tables</strong> — Service or subscription plan comparisons</li>
		</ul>

		<h3>How many products can I include in a comparison table?</h3>
		<p>
			This depends on your plan. Free plan users can include up to 5 products
			per table, Pro plan users can include up to 20, and Enterprise plan
			users have unlimited products per table.
		</p>

		<h3>Can I highlight specific features or products?</h3>
		<p>
			Yes. Pro and Enterprise plans include feature highlighting, allowing
			you to draw attention to specific rows or columns in your comparison
			tables.
		</p>

		<h2>Design & Customization</h2>

		<h3>Can I customize the look of my comparison tables?</h3>
		<p>
			Absolutely. Compare Wise includes pre-built design themes you can apply
			in one click, or you can customize every detail: colors, fonts, spacing,
			column widths, and more. Every table can match your brand identity.
		</p>

		<h3>Does Compare Wise support responsive design?</h3>
		<p>
			Yes. All comparison tables created with Compare Wise are fully responsive and
			automatically adjust to look great on desktop, tablet, and mobile
			devices.
		</p>

		<h3>Can I preview my tables before publishing?</h3>
		<p>
			Yes. Compare Wise provides a live preview feature that shows you exactly
			how your comparison table will appear on your storefront. You can preview on
			different screen sizes before going live.
		</p>

		<h2>Billing & Plans</h2>

		<h3>Is there a free plan?</h3>
		<p>
			Yes. Compare Wise offers a Free plan that includes basic comparison
			tables with up to 5 products per table. It's a great way to try the
			app before committing to a paid plan.
		</p>

		<h3>What do Pro and Enterprise plans include?</h3>
		<p>
			Pro and Enterprise plans unlock more products per table, custom columns,
			feature highlighting, scheduled comparisons, and access to analytics.
			Enterprise also includes priority support and custom
			integration options. See our
			<a href="/compare-wise/pricing">pricing page</a> for full details.
		</p>

		<h3>How does billing work?</h3>
		<p>
			Billing is handled through the Shopify App Store. Your subscription is
			billed monthly alongside your Shopify invoice. You can manage your plan
			and view billing history directly from the Compare Wise dashboard.
		</p>

		<h3>Can I change or cancel my plan at any time?</h3>
		<p>
			Yes. You can upgrade, downgrade, or cancel your plan at any time from
			the app's billing settings. Changes take effect immediately, and any
			prorated amount is handled through Shopify's billing system.
		</p>

		<h2>Technical</h2>

		<h3>Does Compare Wise slow down my store?</h3>
		<p>
			No. Compare Wise's theme extension loads comparison tables asynchronously, so it
			does not impact your store's page load speed or Core Web Vitals.
		</p>

		<h3>Is my data secure?</h3>
		<p>
			Yes. All data is encrypted in transit and at rest. We follow Shopify's
			security best practices and undergo regular security audits. See our
			<a href="/compare-wise/privacy">privacy policy</a> for full details.
		</p>

		<h3>What happens if I uninstall Compare Wise?</h3>
		<p>
			When you uninstall, the theme extension is automatically removed from
			your store and comparison tables stop displaying. Your table data is deleted
			from our servers within 30 days. You can export your configurations
			before uninstalling if needed.
		</p>
	</TextSection>

	<CtaCardSection
		background="var(--theme-surface-2)"
		color="var(--theme-on-surface-2)"
	>
		<h2>Still have questions?</h2>
		<p>
			Our support team is ready to help.
		</p>
		<Button href="mailto:miprio101@gmail.com">Contact Support</Button>
	</CtaCardSection>
</Layout>
